      "comment_id" : 46110449,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I used this to load resources and this is where it failed. Specifically, it failed when I was running Maven test class - at that point, class in my project was trying to load resources from <code>&#47;target&#47;test-classes</code> instead of <code>&#47;target&#47;classes</code>. The problem was solved by using <code>new MyClass().getClass().getResource(&quot;...&quot;)</code> - or just <code>this.getClass ...</code> if in instantiated context."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11683,
      "reputation" : 1520502,
      "user_id" : 22656,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 86,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6d8ebb117e8d83d74ea95fbdd0f87e13?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Jon Skeet",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/22656/jon-skeet"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 211,
    "last_activity_date" : 1224710109,
    "creation_date" : 1224710109,
    "answer_id" : 227569,
    "question_id" : 227486,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Here's an example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>package foo;\n\npublic class Test\n{\n    public static void main(String[] args)\n    {\n        ClassLoader loader = Test.class.getClassLoader();\n        System.out.println(loader.getResource(\"foo/Test.class\"));\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This printed out:</p>\n\n<pre><code>file:/C:/Users/Jon/Test/foo/Test.class\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
