    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is what we use:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static String getClassResource(Class&lt;?&gt; klass) {\n  return klass.getClassLoader().getResource(\n     klass.getName().replace('.', '/') + \".class\").toString();\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This will work depending on the ClassLoader implementation: \n<code>getClass().getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation()</code></p>\n"
  }, {
